race.description: Commins Hendriks - Australia Day Cup Handicap
race.comment: PRIDE OF JEZZA (7) has returned in great order this campaign and went better than the last run suggests in town, working home nicely from an awkward spot. His first three runs of the prep were strong efforts here, producing two wins. Ticking along superbly and should relish the rise to 2000m. Leading player. SEA STRIKE (6) hasn't threatened in his two runs back but has been tackling stiffer opposition. Much better placed this time and should be nearing a peak third-up. Gets in low at the weights and reunites with winning hoop. Have to take seriously. DYNAMIC ONE (4) was back near his best last time when a close third at Cowra. Has been mixing his form this prep but gets a key booking in McDougall from a handy draw and backs up quickly. Genuine hope if he's present on-song. GATCHAN (5) drifted well back and failed to finish it off last start when sixth, over 2400m at Kembla Grange. Will find this a bit easier and will be looking to settle much closer to the action this time.
